g these to the application routes, and considering direct correspondence. This may yield a more efficient mapping strategy.\n\n\n**Confirming Route Resolution**\n\nI've been looking closer at `app-shell.tsx` and now have found the `onNavigate` implementation, specifically `handleLinkChange`. This allows me to see the route resolution with the route map. It seems that if I can map the correct tab IDs, such as \"ai-operations\", \"analytics\", and \"projects\" into `clientLinkToRoute`, I can fix the broken links. This seems like a better pathway.\n\n\n**Confirming Portal Routes**\n\nNow I'm verifying the corrected route mappings! Changing the routes to `\"billing\"`, `\"analytics\"`, `\"governance\"`, and `\"support\"` solves the navigation issue. I am confirming these routes now, and I believe I have now fixed the broken links. This clarifies the expected correspondence between the navigation and available pages. I need to be sure that the command palette can properly handle navigation. Now, let's explore if this is handled the same way with the admin command palette.\n\n\n"}}
