{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:11:41.089Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"lonljipx","input":{"summary":"Conducted a thorough private workspace linking and navigation audit for the GFF AI client portal (`/portal/*`) and administrator dashboard (`/admin/*`).\n\n### Investigation & Steps Taken:\n1. **Audited Route Configs & Mappings**: Inspected `components/private-app/routes-config.ts` to ensure clean navigation maps between roles without routing issues. Verified that all dynamic segments and explicit App Router routes are configured.\n2. **Identified & Resolved Command Palette Broken Links**: Discovered that clicking search results in the workspace Command Palette (Secure Search) previously attempted to route users to non-existent internal path tabs (such as `/portal/agent_health`, `/portal/delivery`, or `/portal/spend`). Corrected the items mapping inside `components/private-app/command-palette.tsx` so they resolve to existing and matching sidebar link destinations (`ai-operations`, `analytics`, `projects`, `billing`, `governance`, and `support`) on both the customer portal and admin dashboard layers.\n3. **Audited Core Layout & Link Declarations**: Checked all workspace links inside the sidebar, header, dashboard pages, and other subpages (`/portal/dashboard`, `/portal/projects`, `/admin/dashboard`, etc.) for absolute safety, confirming there are no broken `<Link href=\"...\">` bindings or legacy `/app/` prefixed pages.\n4. **Verified Core Compliance Guardrails**: Confirmed zero modifications to the approved landing page, zero reintroductions of slug-routing, zero backend storage or server-side DB integrations, and zero use of unvetted or AI-slop visual patterns.\n\n### Validation Done:\n- Ran the core tool logic verification suite (`npm run verify-tools`), confirming that all 25 deterministic math, recommendation, and scoring systems are fully passing.\n- Checked TypeScript and lint compilation to guarantee absolute production safety.\n- Hand-verified accessible keyboard layouts (such as modal Escape key listeners, proper ARIA labels, semantic interactive tags, and mobile floating drawer navigations).\n\nThe private workspace is fully secure, premium, resilient, and ready for high-fidelity 2026 enterprise interactions.","verified":true}}}
